status: MARC21-007: Kind of cutting of sound recording
Kind of cutting of the grooves used on a disc.

definition (en): Vertical cutting, with no lateral information intended for reproduction.
scope note (en): All cylinders and some early discs have this cutting.

definition (en): Cutting containing lateral information intended for reproduction. Such discs may also have vertical components intended for reproduction.
scope note (en): Most contemporary discs (i.e., all quadraphonic discs and nearly all stereophonic discs) contain both vertical and laterial information and are coded l. Monographic discs are normally lateral only.

definition (en): Item is not a disc or a cylinder.
scope note (en): Includes compact audio discs as they are pitted rather than cut.

definition (en): Kind of cutting is not known.
